  "informal_statement": "For every natural number n, 4*n is not prime: n=0 gives 0 (not prime by definition), and n>=1 gives an even number >=4 which has 2 as a proper divisor, so it cannot be prime.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Assume 4*n is prime. Since 2 | 4*n, primality forces 2 = 1 or 2 = 4*n; the first is false and the second combined with n being a natural number is resolved by omega.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem four_mul_not_prime (n : ℕ) : ¬ Nat.Prime (4 * n)",
